messages.content:
=`Analyze the following Outlook email for phishing risk and output a single line that begins with:
LABEL: SAFE | SUSPICIOUS | CRITICAL  (choose one).
Keep the rest concise and point to the main indicators.

From: ${$json.fromName} <${$json.fromAddress}>
Reply-To: ${$json.replyToAddress}
Subject: ${$json.subject}
Importance: ${$json.importance} | Attachments: ${$json.hasAttachments}
Auth Results: SPF ${$json.auth.spf || 'unknown'}, DKIM ${$json.auth.dkim || 'unknown'}, DMARC ${$json.auth.dmarc || 'unknown'}

Body Preview:
${$json.bodyPreview}

Body (truncated):
${$json.safeText}

Suspicious headers to consider (truncated JSON):
${JSON.stringify($json.headers).slice(0, 3000)}

Rules:
- If financial urgency, credential harvest, spoofed display names, mismatched reply-to domains, or failed SPF/DKIM/DMARC are present, lean CRITICAL.
- Otherwise if anything looks off, choose SUSPICIOUS.
- Otherwise SAFE.
- Respond EXACTLY one line. Start with: LABEL: <value> — then a 1–2 sentence rationale.`
